                    <h3>Understanding Acne:</h3>
                    <p class="fst-italic"></p>
                    <p>Acne occurs when hair follicles become clogged with oil and dead skin cells, leading to the formation of pimples, blackheads, and whiteheads. Hormonal changes, genetics, diet, stress, and certain medications can all contribute to the development of acne. Understanding the underlying causes is crucial in devising an effective treatment plan.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-lg-4 text-center order-1 order-lg-2">
                    <img src="assets/img/TypesAcne.jpg" alt="" class="img-fluid">
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="tab-pane" id="tab-2">
                <div class="row gy-4">
                  <div class="col-lg-8 details order-2 order-lg-1">
                    <h3>Topical Treatments:</h3>
                    <p class="fst-italic"></p>
                    <p>Over-the-counter topical treatments can be effective in reducing acne symptoms. Products containing benzoyl peroxide work by killing acne-causing bacteria and reducing inflammation. Similarly, salicylic acid helps to exfoliate the skin and unclog pores, preventing new breakouts from forming. Apply these treatments sparingly to affected areas to avoid dryness and irritation.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-lg-4 text-center order-1 order-lg-2">
                    <img src="assets/img/TropicalTreatments.jpg" alt="" class="img-fluid">
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="tab-pane" id="tab-3">
                <div class="row gy-4">
                  <div class="col-lg-8 details order-2 order-lg-1">
                    <h3>Prescription Medications:</h3>
                    <p class="fst-italic"></p>
                    <p>For more severe cases of acne, prescription medications may be necessary. Topical retinoids, such as tretinoin or adapalene, help to unclog pores and promote cell turnover, preventing new breakouts. Oral antibiotics are often prescribed to reduce inflammation and kill bacteria. In some cases, hormonal therapy or isotretinoin (Accutane) may be recommended for long-term management of acne.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-lg-4 text-center order-1 order-lg-2">
                    <img src="assets/img/Prescription.jpg" alt="" class="img-fluid">
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="tab-pane" id="tab-4">
                <div class="row gy-4">
                  <div class="col-lg-8 details order-2 order-lg-1">
                    <h3>Lifestyle Changes:</h3>
                    <p class="fst-italic"></p>
                    <p>In addition to skincare and medication, certain lifestyle changes can help improve acne symptoms. Avoiding excessive sun exposure and using non-comedogenic sunscreen can prevent further irritation and sun damage. Eating a balanced diet rich in fruits, vegetables, and whole grains can support overall skin health. Managing stress through relaxation techniques like yoga or meditation may also help reduce acne flare-ups.</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-lg-4 text-center order-1 order-lg-2">
                    <img src="assets/img/Fruits.jpg" alt="" class="img-fluid">
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="tab-pane" id="tab-5">
                <div class="row gy-4">
                  <div class="col-lg-8 details order-2 order-lg-1">
                    <h3>Conclusion:</h3>
                    <p class="fst-italic"></p>
                    <p>Acne can be a challenging condition to deal with, but it is manageable with the right approach and treatment. By understanding the underlying causes of acne and implementing a comprehensive skincare routine, you can effectively control breakouts and achieve clear, healthy skin. Remember to be patient and persistent in your efforts, and don't hesitate to seek professional help if needed. With dedication and perseverance, you can overcome acne and regain your confidence and self-esteem. 
